- tools/dev/prune-worktrees.ts: the merged-guard uses `git branch --merged
  main`, which does not recognize squash merges (squash creates a new commit
  with no merge ancestry). This affects ALL feature branches that merge to
  main via GitHub squash-merge — not just h/v3 slices. Hit twice: 2026-07-16
  cleaning ui-polish-7, 2026-07-17 cleaning untitled-docs wave-1 worktrees
  (four branches, all manual). Fallback is manual drop-db + worktree remove
  + branch -D. Teach the resolver to use the PR's merge status via `gh`
  (or detect squash-merge content equivalence) instead of relying on git
  merge ancestry.

- tools/dev/prune-worktrees.ts: `--auto` also misses closed-not-merged PRs
  and integration-lane branches that were squash-merged into a parent feature
  branch (not main). Hit 2026-07-23: ~176 stale test databases and 5
  merged-lane worktrees required manual cleanup. The resolver should query
  PR merge status via `gh` for the general case, not just `git branch
  --merged main`.
